## [HOME](scrolls/home)

# server

## PI setup:
 
Get a SD card with 8 GB or more storage and a SD card USB reader

Download and install, then use the Raspberry Pi Imager:

[https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/](https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/)

Turn on the pi click through all the things, put it on the wifi network. 


## Old laptop setup:

You will need a thumb drive. Follow the instructions below to install Ubuntu

[https://ubuntu.com instructions](https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/install-ubuntu-desktop#1-overview)


## Server install:

Open a terminal and type the following

```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2 -y
sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php -y
cd /var/www/html
sudo rm index.html
sudo apt-get install arduino
sudo apt install python3-matplotlib
sudo apt-get install python3-scipy
sudo pip3 install --upgrade pip
reboot
sudo pip3 install jupyter
sudo apt-get install gnuradio
```

Then locate the folder /var/www/html and put other folders in there and put all your media in there.  Put in *everything*.  To run a Jupyter notebook in a given folder, open the terminal and move to the correct folder before typing

```
jupyter notebook
```
and you will have a notebook which is in the proper web folder. Jupyter notebooks are JSON documents.
